bg.x2d.utils

Class Multimap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • bg.x2d.utils.Multimap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type for keys
    V - the type for values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>

    public class Multimap<K,V>
extends AbstractMap<K,V>
    Provides a Map that maps multiple values to a single key. This map is backed by a Hashtable that maps a single key to a dynamic array of values. All read/write methods of Multimap are synchronized so objects may be modified asynchronously by multiple threads.
    Author:
    Brian Groenke
